posts.name: icemannie
posts.cooked:
Took another look this morning, This error is almost certainly your problem. Error at com.pathplanner.lib.auto.AutoBuilder.configure(AutoBuilder.java:72): Auto builder has already been configured. This is likely in error. at com.pathplanner.lib.auto.AutoBuilder.configure(AutoBuilder.java:72) at frc.robot.subsystems.SwerveSubsystem.setupPathPlanner(SwerveSubsystem.java:174) at frc.robot.subsystems.SwerveSubsystem.(SwerveSubsystem.java:87) at frc.robot.RobotContainer.(RobotContainer.java:68) at frc.robot.Robot.(Robot.java:29) at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:370) at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.lambda$startRobot$1(RobotBase.java:490) at java.base/java.lang.Thread.run(Thread.java:840) Also getting multiple Warning at com.pathplanner.lib.auto.NamedCommands.getCommand(NamedCommands.java:65): PathPlanner attempted to create a command ‘Elevator First Pipe’ that has not been registered with NamedCommands.registerCommand Your SwerveSubsystem construction looks different from the 2025 example YAGSL , which has SwerveSubsystem in a swervedrive subfolder. Tried changing that unsuccessfully. Recommend you update WPILIB and your vendor dependencies and make sure PathPlanner is the latest.

Then download the latest YAGSL example from GitHub - FRC-9438/Yagsl_2025 , and test some simple NamedCommands like

Then copy over your swerve jsons, subsystems, commands etc.

posts.name: icemannie
posts.cooked: You can see the errors if you run Simulation. Add  DriverStation.silenceJoystickConnectionWarning(true); to RobotContainer to filter the messages. Pathplanner docs are very specific about NamedCommands being before any other PathPlanner actions in your code. The error message is telling you that something is happening with PathPlanner that it doesn’t like. I’ve tried patching your code with what the new YAGSL example has without success. Where did you get the way you are configuring the SwerveSubsystem?
